{"type":"message","id":"5e844436","parentId":"8643ebe0","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:34:29.171Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_KedzT79QwZpFG7Nh4bDezSuU|fc_0e77e8da73e64f160169d1e65153b48197938ed5ced7ee4ee8","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Service: systemd (disabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-05.log\n\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH is not set; the daemon should use a minimal PATH.\nConfig (cli): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=40062 (env/config)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:40062\nRecommendation: run \"openclaw doctor\" (or \"openclaw doctor --repair\").\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:40062/app/trim-openclaw/default/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nRuntime: unknown (systemctl --user unavailable: Failed to connect to bus: Permission denied\nFailed to read server status: Transport endpoint is not connected)\nRPC probe: ok\n\nsystemd user services unavailable.\nsystemd user services are unavailable; install/enable systemd or run the gateway under your supervisor.\nOn a headless server (SSH/no desktop session): run `sudo loginctl enable-linger $(whoami)` to persist your systemd user session across logins.\nAlso ensure XDG_RUNTIME_DIR is set: `export XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/$(id -u)`, then retry.\nIf you're in a container, run the gateway in the foreground instead of `openclaw gateway`.\n\nListening: 127.0.0.1:40062\nTroubles: run openclaw status\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2720,"aggregated":"Service: systemd (disabled)\nFile logs: /tmp/openclaw/openclaw-2026-04-05.log\n\nService config looks out of date or non-standard.\nService config issue: Gateway service PATH is not set; the daemon should use a minimal PATH.\nConfig (cli): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\nConfig (service): ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json\n\nGateway: bind=loopback (127.0.0.1), port=40062 (env/config)\nProbe target: ws://127.0.0.1:40062\nRecommendation: run \"openclaw doctor\" (or \"openclaw doctor --repair\").\nDashboard: http://127.0.0.1:40062/app/trim-openclaw/default/\nProbe note: Loopback-only gateway; only local clients can connect.\n\nRuntime: unknown (systemctl --user unavailable: Failed to connect to bus: Permission denied\nFailed to read server status: Transport endpoint is not connected)\nRPC probe: ok\n\nsystemd user services unavailable.\nsystemd user services are unavailable; install/enable systemd or run the gateway under your supervisor.\nOn a headless server (SSH/no desktop session): run `sudo loginctl enable-linger $(whoami)` to persist your systemd user session across logins.\nAlso ensure XDG_RUNTIME_DIR is set: `export XDG_RUNTIME_DIR=/run/user/$(id -u)`, then retry.\nIf you're in a container, run the gateway in the foreground instead of `openclaw gateway`.\n\nListening: 127.0.0.1:40062\nTroubles: run openclaw status\nTroubleshooting: https://docs.openclaw.ai/troubleshooting","cwd":"/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775363669167}}
{"type":"message","id":"ea373c5d","parentId":"5e844436","timestamp":"2026-04-05T04:34:40.516Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] gateway 其实**已经在跑**了。\n\n我刚查到的是：\n\n- **RPC probe: ok**\n- **Listening: `127.0.0.1:40062`**\n- Dashboard 也有：\n  `http://127.0.0.1:40062/app/trim-openclaw/default/`\n\n所以不是“没起来”，而是：\n\n## 当前状态\n- **gateway 已运行**\n- 但它现在是 **loopback only**\n  - 只监听 `127.0.0.1`\n  - 也就是**只有本机能连**\n- 同时 systemd 用户服务这层不太健康\n  - `systemctl --user` 不可用\n  - 所以它不像是被一个标准、持久的用户服务优雅托管着\n\n---\n\n## 这句“继续把 gateway 跑起来”我理解成两种可能\n\n### 情况 A：你只是想确认它有没有活着\n那答案是：\n\n**活着，而且现在就在跑。**\n\n### 情况 B：你是想让它“稳定长期跑、可重启后继续、别半死不活”\n那现在还**不算完全理想**，因为：\n- service config 看起来有点旧/非标准\n- systemd user services unavailable\n- 官方也提示：\n  - `openclaw doctor`\n  - 或 `openclaw doctor --repair`\n\n---\n\n## 所以我建议下一步\n如果你的目标是“别只是活着，要活得稳”，我建议继续做：\n\n### 先做无损体检\n运行：\n- `openclaw doctor`\n\n它会告诉我们：\n- gateway 配置哪儿不规范\n- service 哪儿不对\n- 能不能自动修\n\n### 如果你要我直接推进\n我下一步可以帮你：\n1. 先跑 `openclaw doctor`\n2. 看是否建议 `--repair`\n3. 再决定要不要修\n\n---\n\n## 最短结论\n**gateway 已经跑起来了。**  \n但如果你要的是“稳定托管、配置规范、长期可靠”，那**还没完全收拾干净**。\n\n你如果要我继续，我建议下一步就是：\n\n**查 doctor**","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0e77e8da73e64f160169d1e65780a481979b0574cc3259edf3\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openai","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":56423,"output":487,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":56910,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775363669172,"responseId":"resp_0e77e8da73e64f160169d1e656373c81978a28d984b53ab347"}}
