at history since last reply (untrusted, for context):\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/extraction-prompts.ts:17:Target Output Language: auto (detect from recent messages)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/memory-categories.ts:29:/** Categories whose facts can be replaced over time without deleting history. */\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/reflection-retry.ts:71:  /context window/i,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/smart-extractor.ts:635:    // preventing superseded history from crowding out the current fact.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/smart-metadata.ts:437:  if (Array.isArray(capped.history) && capped.history.length > MAX_HISTORY) {\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/smart-metadata.ts:438:    capped.history = capped.history.slice(-MAX_HISTORY);\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/tools.ts:1043:        \"Update an existing memory. For preferences/entities, changing text creates a new version (supersede) to preserve history. Metadata-only changes (importance, category) update in-place.\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/tools.ts:1148:          // text must go through supersede to preserve the history chain.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/src/tools.ts:1804:          \"Archive a memory to remove it from default auto-recall while preserving history.\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/smart-metadata-v2.mjs:108:console.log(\"\\nTest 7: stringifySmartMetadata caps sources/history/relations...\");\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/smart-metadata-v2.mjs:112:    history: Array.from({ length: 60 }, (_, i) => `hist_${i}`),\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/smart-metadata-v2.mjs:117:assert.ok(serialized.history.length <= 50, `history should be capped at 50, got ${serialized.history.length}`);\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/temporal-facts.test.mjs:167:    console.log(\"\\nTest 2: supersede preserves history but invalidates the old fact...\");\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/temporal-facts.test.mjs:196:    console.log(\"  ✅ old fact is retained as history and marked inactive\");\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/test/temporal-facts.test.mjs:257:    // Verify there are now 10 total entries (1 original + 1 current + 8 history)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:251:         * 8. history\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:261:        addListener(event: \"history\", listener: (history: string[]) => void): this;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:270:        emit(event: \"history\", history: string[]): boolean;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:279:        on(event: \"history\", listener: (history: string[]) => void): this;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:288:        once(event: \"history\", listener: (history: string[]) => void): this;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:297:        prependListener(event: \"history\", listener: (history: string[]) => void): this;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:306:        prependOnceListener(event: \"history\", listener: (history: string[]) => void): this;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:336:         * Initial list of history lines.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:338:         * otherwise the history caching mechanism is not initialized at all.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:341:        history?: string[] | undefined;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:343:         * Maximum number of history lines retained.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:344:         * To disable the history set this value to `0`.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:346:         * otherwise the history caching mechanism is not initialized at all.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:349:        historySize?: number | undefined;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/readline.d.ts:351:         * If `true`, when a new input line added to the history list duplicates an older one,\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/repl.d.ts:312:         * Initializes a history log file for the REPL instance. When executing the\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/repl.d.ts:313:         * Node.js binary and using the command-line REPL, a history file is initialized\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/repl.d.ts:315:         * programmatically. Use this method to initialize a history log file when working\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/repl.d.ts:318:         * @param historyPath the path to the history file\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/repl.d.ts:319:         * @param callback called when history writes are ready or upon error\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/@types/node/test.d.ts:1467:             * Resets the call history of the mock function.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/typescript.js:197233:    // no versions earlier than min version will maintain change history\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/typesMap.json:181:        \"history\": \"history\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/typesMap.json:182:        \"History\": \"history\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/typesMap.json:314:        \"native.history\": \"history\",\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17847: * The **`History`** interface of the History API allows manipulation of the browser _session history_, that is the pages visited in the tab or frame that the current page is loaded in.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17853:     * The **`length`** read-only property of the History interface returns an integer representing the number of entries in the session history, including the currently loaded page.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17859:     * The **`scrollRestoration`** property of the History interface allows web applications to explicitly set default scroll restoration behavior on history navigation.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17865:     * The **`state`** read-only property of the History interface returns a value representing the state at the top of the history stack.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17871:     * The **`back()`** method of the History interface causes the browser to move back one page in the session history.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17877:     * The **`forward()`** method of the History interface causes the browser to move forward one page in the session history.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17883:     * The **`go()`** method of the History interface loads a specific page from the session history.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17889:     * The **`pushState()`** method of the History interface adds an entry to the browser's session history stack.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:17895:     * The **`replaceState()`** method of the History interface modifies the current history entry, replacing it with the state object and URL passed in the method parameters.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21243:     * The **`entry`** read-only property of the NavigationActivation interface contains a NavigationHistoryEntry object representing the history entry for the inbound ('to') document in the navigation.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21249:     * The **`from`** read-only property of the NavigationActivation interface contains a NavigationHistoryEntry object representing the history entry for the outgoing ('from') document in the navigation.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21272: * The **`NavigationHistoryEntry`** interface of the Navigation API represents a single navigation history entry.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21278:     * The **`id`** read-only property of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns the `id` of the history entry, or an empty string if current document is not fully active.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21284:     * The **`index`** read-only property of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns the index of the history entry in the history entries list (that is, the list returned by Navigation.entries()), or `-1` if the entry does not appear in the list or if current document is not fully active.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21290:     * The **`key`** read-only property of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns the `key` of the history entry, or an empty string if current document is not fully active.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21298:     * The **`sameDocument`** read-only property of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns `true` if this history entry is for the same `document` as the current Document value and current document is fully active, or `false` otherwise.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21304:     * The **`url`** read-only property of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns the absolute URL of this history entry.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:21310:     * The **`getState()`** method of the NavigationHistoryEntry interface returns a clone of the developer-supplied state associated with this history entry.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:22518:     * The **`activation`** read-only property of the PageSwapEvent interface contains a NavigationActivation object containing the navigation type and current and destination document history entries for a same-origin navigation.\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:36422:     * The `Window.history` read-only property returns a reference to the History object, which provides an interface for manipulating the browser _session history_ (pages visited in the tab or frame that the current page is loaded in).\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:36424:     * [MDN Reference](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/Window/history)\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:36426:    readonly history: History;\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:38458: * The `Window.history` read-only property returns a reference to the History object, which provides an interface for manipulating the browser _session history_ (pages visited in the tab or frame that the current page is loaded in).\n/vol1/@apphome/trim.openclaw/data/workspace/plugins/memory-lancedb-pro/node_modules/typescript/lib/lib.dom.d.ts:38460: